name: nrel-gis-data-u-s-atlantic-coast-offshore-windspeed-90m-height-high-resolution-dcc82
notes:
This dataset is a geographic shapefile generated from the original raster data. The original raster data resolution is a 200-meter cell size. The data provide an estimate of annual average wind speed at 90 meter height above surface for specific offshore regions of the United States.  To learn more, please see the [ Assessment of Offshore Wind Energy Resources for the United States](http://nrelpubs.nrel.gov/WebtopSecure/ws/nich/int/nrel/Record?rpp=25&upp=0&m=3&w=NATIVE%28%27AUTHOR+ph+words+%27%27Heimiller%27%27%27%29&order=native%28%27pubyear%2FDescend%27%29 "NREL Publication").

These data were produced in cooperation with U.S. Department of Energy, and have been validated by NREL. To download state wind resource maps, visit [Wind Powering America](http://www.windpoweringamerica.gov/windmaps/offshore.asp).

In order to ensure the downloadable shapefile is current, please compare the date updated on this page to the last updated date on the [NREL GIS Wind Data](http://www.nrel.gov/gis/data_wind.html "NREL GIS Wind Data webpage") webpage.
